---
import Navigation from "../components/Navigation.astro";
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Projects | William64.com</title>
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="Explore William Sutton's software engineering projects, from systems programming to web development and reverse engineering."
    />

    <!-- Strategic Preloading -->
    <link rel="preload" href="/styles.css" as="style" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />

    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles.css" />
  </head>
  <body class="bg-black text-green-400 font-mono">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto p-4">
      <header class="border-b border-green-700 pb-4 mb-8">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-2">William64.com</h1>
        <Navigation />
      </header>

      <main>
        <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Projects</h1>

        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl border-b border-green-700 pb-2 mb-6">
            Featured Projects
          </h2>

          <div class="project-card mb-10">
            <div class="project-header">
              <div class="title-bar">
                <span class="controls">
                  <span class="circle"></span>
                  <span class="circle"></span>
                  <span class="circle"></span>
                </span>
                <span class="title">tpc-server</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="project-body p-4">
              <pre class="mb-4 whitespace-pre-wrap break-words overflow-x-auto">
$ tpc-server --help

A Python MCP server for structured thought/plan/changelog management
with SQLite database backend. Provides tools for tracking technical
decision making and project evolution over time.

Features:
- Thought/Plan/Change record keeping
- MCP protocol implementation
- SQLite data persistence
- Web interface for visualization
              </pre>
              <div class="project-meta">
                <div class="technologies flex flex-wrap gap-2">
                  <span class="label">Technologies:</span>
                  <span class="tech-tag">Python</span>
                  <span class="tech-tag">MCP</span>
                  <span class="tech-tag">SQLite</span>
                  <span class="tech-tag">FastAPI</span>
                </div>
                <div class="links mt-2 flex flex-wrap gap-4">
                  <a
                    href="https://github.com/suttonwilliamd/tpc-server"
                    class="project-link">GitHub &rarr;</a
                  >
                  <a href="/tpc-server" class="project-link"
                    >Live Demo &rarr;</a
                  >
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="project-card mb-10">
            <div class="project-header">
              <div class="title-bar">
                <span class="controls">
                  <span class="circle"></span>
                  <span class="circle"></span>
                  <span class="circle"></span>
                </span>
                <span class="title">Token Viewer</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="project-body p-4">
              <pre class="mb-4 whitespace-pre-wrap break-words overflow-x-auto">
$ token-viewer --help
           
An interactive tool for exploring GPT-2 tokens, allowing users to visualize
the relationship between token IDs and their decoded string representations.
Built with Astro for static site generation and React for client-side interactivity,
this tool demonstrates efficient browser-based decoding using the
@nem035/gpt-3-encoder package.
              </pre>
              <div class="project-meta">
                <div class="technologies flex flex-wrap gap-2">
                  <span class="label">Technologies:</span>
                  <span class="tech-tag">Astro</span>
                  <span class="tech-tag">React</span>
                  <span class="tech-tag">JavaScript</span>
                </div>
                <div class="links mt-2 flex flex-wrap gap-4">
                  <a
                    href="https://github.com/suttonwilliamd/token-viewer"
                    class="project-link">GitHub &rarr;</a
                  >
                  <a href="/token-viewer" class="project-link"
                    >Live Demo &rarr;</a
                  >
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl border-b border-green-700 pb-2 mb-6">
            Web Projects
          </h2>

          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
            <div class="mini-project-card">
              <h3 class="text-xl mb-2">William64.com</h3>
              <p class="mb-3">
                This website - built with Astro.js, featuring a
                terminal-inspired design with static generation.
              </p>
              <div class="technologies flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-2">
                <span class="tech-tag">Astro</span>
                <span class="tech-tag">TypeScript</span>
                <span class="tech-tag">React</span>
              </div>
              <a href="#" class="project-link">Source Code &rarr;</a>
            </div>

            <div class="mini-project-card">
              <h3 class="text-xl mb-2">RetroVisualizer</h3>
              <p class="mb-3">
                Data visualization tool inspired by vintage computer graphics,
                built with modern web technologies.
              </p>
              <div class="technologies flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-2">
                <span class="tech-tag">JavaScript</span>
                <span class="tech-tag">Canvas API</span>
                <span class="tech-tag">D3.js</span>
              </div>
              <a href="#" class="project-link">View Project &rarr;</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>
      </main>

      <Footer />
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
```

Key responsiveness improvements:

1. Added `whitespace-pre-wrap` and `break-words` to the `<pre>` elements to prevent horizontal overflow and allow text wrapping

2. Added `overflow-x-auto` to the pre elements as a fallback in case there are any unbreakable strings

3. Added `flex flex-wrap gap-2` to the technologies sections to ensure tags wrap properly on small screens

4. Added `flex flex-wrap gap-4` to the links sections to ensure links stack properly on narrow screens

These changes will ensure the page is fully responsive and doesn't create horizontal scrollbars, maintaining consistency with your about page styling.
import Navigation from "../components/Navigation.astro";
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
